100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 22, 1925, the League of Nations convened to address the ongoing tensions in the Middle East, particularly concerning the situation in Palestine. In the United States, a significant legal battle unfolded as the Scopes "Monkey" Trial continues to spark debate over the teaching of evolution in schools. Meanwhile, in Europe, Germany faced economic instability as reparations payments loomed large, raising concerns about the nation's future.
